# config/gh-accounts - per-repo GitHub account routing for bin/fm-gh.sh.
#
# Copy this file to config/gh-accounts (which is LOCAL and gitignored) and edit it.
# The real map is captain-local: it names your accounts, so it is never committed.
#
# The gh CLI keeps one active account at a time, but the fleet spans repos owned by
# different accounts. fm-gh.sh resolves the owner of the target repo - from an
# explicit `-R owner/repo`, otherwise from the `origin` remote of the current repo -
# looks the owner up here, and switches the active gh account to the mapped one
# (idempotently) before running the command.
#
# Format: one `owner=account` per line.
#   owner    the repo owner as it appears in the URL: github.com/OWNER/repo
#   account  the gh username to switch to, as shown by `gh auth status`
# `#` starts a comment; blank lines are ignored. Whitespace around `=` is tolerated.
# An owner with no line here is left on whatever account is active (fm-gh warns, but
# never fails), so only list owners that need a non-default account.
#
# Example - a work org and the firstmate fork live under one account, an NLP org
# under another:
# acme-web=alice-work
# alice=alice-work
# nlp-platform=alice-research
